{% block help%}
<center><h3>Personalized Notes</h3></center>
<p>You are free to write any personalized notes in the <em>Description</em> box. These notes will be displayed in the <em>Details</em> box when viewing Circos, and can serve as future reference.</p>

<center><h3>Files upload</h3></center>
<p>You can either upload a <b>.zip</b> or a <b>.tar</b> package. This package must contain all the files needed to generate your Circos, i.e.</p>
<p><ul>
  <li><font color="#6495ED">circos.conf</font>: this is your main configuration file. It can contain some <em>&lt&ltinclude&gt&gt</em> parameters. You do not have to specify a <em>file</em> nor a <em>dir</em> parameter.</li>
 <li><font color="#6495ED">other .conf</font>: all the configuration files that you referred to in your circos.conf</li>
  <li><font color="#6495ED">karyotype.conf</font>: file with the desired karyotype</li>
 <li><font color="#6495ED">.txt</font>: all the data files needed for your track(s), links and/or labels. 
</ul></p>
<p>Every file need to be formmatted according to the Circos conventions. When writing the path to one of your data files, only write its name, no path needed.</p>
<p><pre>&ltplots&gt<br>  ...<br>  &ltplot&gt<br>    type  = histogram<br>    file  = hist1.txt<br>    ...<br>  &lt/plot&gt<br>&lt/plots&gt</pre></p>
<p>Please do not use sub-folder(s) in your package: only multiple single files.</p>
{% endblock %}

{% block header %}
<h1> Upload configuration package <small>.tar, .tar.gz, .zip</small></hi> 
{% endblock %}

